adverseReactions_original:
Celecoxib capsules are contraindicated in the following patients:



                        •Known hypersensitivity (e.g., anaphylactic reactions and serious skin reactions) to celecoxib, any components of the drug product [see Warnings and Precautions (5.7
                           , 5.9)
                        ].

                        •History of asthma, urticaria, or other allergic-type reactions after taking aspirin or other NSAIDs. Severe, sometimes fatal, anaphylactic reactions to NSAIDs, have been reported in such patients [see Warnings and Precautions (5.7
                           , 5.8)
                        ].

                        •In the setting of CABG surgery [see  Warnings and Precautions (5.1)
                        ].

                        •In patients who have demonstrated allergic-type reactions to sulfonamides [see Warnings and Precautions (5.7)].
